                <div class="portfolio-description">
                  <p>
                    Using the RAINBO board, my team and I designed a circuit to sync the flashing of multiple LED
                    strips to the bass channel of any song. We designed a Low-pass filter and amplifier circuit (dubbed
                    "LPFA") using circuits.io (now deprecated). The RAINBO board accepts an analog value (output from
                    LPFA board), adds it to the most recent ones. The top 4 values of the 10 most recent ones are
                    averaged, and the output is the number of LEDs that are lit up.
                  </p>
                  <p>
